<TITLE>X-Horn Ground Pickup</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000"  BGCOLOR="#F0F0F0">

<H2>July 08, 2015 - X-Horn Ground Pickup</H2>


<p>


<hr>
<p>
A calculation of X-Horn's relative ground pickup as a function of 
tipping angle, using far-field beam profiles obtained from a previous 
calibration at Princeton.
<p>
We compare the intensity spectra of the ground (assumed to be a 290K blackbody)
over a range of tipping angles, 
alongside the intensity spectra of the atmosphere at the corresponding 
airmasses.  
<p>
We also compare the brightness temperature (Tb) spectra of the ground and 
atmosphere over a range of tipping angles, in the Rayleigh-Jeans regime where 
intensity is linear in temperature. 

<hr>


<H3>1D Profiles</H3>

<p>
<p>
H-plane, 10 GHz, with and without baffle. Linearly interpolated from digitized
calibration plots. 
<p>
<a href="1dprofiles.png">
<img src="1dprofiles.png" width=1300></a>
<hr>
<H3>2D Profiles</H3>
<p>
Gain (dBs) mapped over azimuth and elevation. Beams assumed to be axially 
symmetric.
